{"claim_type": "salt-chemistry", "line_end": 43, "line_start": 43, "page_hint": null, "section": "ABSTRACT", "text": "Wall thickness changes were measured for the Volatility Pilot Plant INOR-8 dissolver after 204 hours of exposure to anhydrous HF and equimolar NaF-LiF fused salt containing 22-52 mole per cent $\\mathsf{ZrF_4}$ at $495 - 655^{\\circ}C$ while Zircaloy-2 dummy fuel elements were being dissolved."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 45, "line_start": 45, "page_hint": null, "section": "ABSTRACT", "text": "For the dissolver, maximum wall thickness losses were noted in the vapor region where a maximum loss of 11 mils was found."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 45, "line_start": 45, "page_hint": null, "section": "ABSTRACT", "text": "This loss corresponds to 0.054 mils/hour, based on HF exposure time, or 17.0 mils/month, based on molten salt residence time."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 78, "line_start": 78, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "The Volatility Pilot Plant has currently completed a series of seven cold dissolution runs using Zircaloy-2 dummy fuel elements according to the head-end procedure of the fused salt Volatility Process."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 78, "line_start": 78, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "A necessary part of that evaluation was the determination of the corrosion losses occurring on INOR-8, the material of construction for the dissolver vessel."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 78, "line_start": 78, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "The nominal composition of INOR-8 is Ni: 71 wt %, Cr: 7 wt %, Fe: 5 wt %, and Mo: 16 wt %."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 78, "line_start": 78, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "Table II details the process conditions for the seven runs and indicates that equimolar NaF-LiF fused salt containing 22-52 mole per cent $\\mathrm{ZrF_4}$ was used at temperatures of $495 - 655^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}$ along with $1160\\mathrm{kg}$ of anhydrous HF to dissolve eight dummy fuel elements."}
{"claim_type": "figure-reference", "line_end": 78, "line_start": 78, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "Figure 1 shows a schematic of the hydrofluorination operation."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 80, "line_start": 80, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "Wall thickness measurements were made prior to the development runs and twice after run T-7 using an ultrasonic thickness measuring device, the \"Vidigage.\" The first measurement after run T-7 followed a 41 hr wash with boiling $0.35\\mathrm{M}$ ammonium oxalate solution; and the second measurement followed a 10 hr rinse with boiling $5\\mathrm{wt}\\% \\mathrm{HNO}_3 - 5\\mathrm{wt}\\% \\mathrm{Al}(\\mathrm{NO}_3)_3$ ."}
{"claim_type": "figure-reference", "line_end": 80, "line_start": 80, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "Figures 2, 3, and 4 present the data obtained and show that measurements were made at $90^{\\circ}$ intervals around the circumference of the dissolver at three inch height increments."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 82, "line_start": 82, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "Although a restricted number of readings were taken on the top cylindrical section of the dissolver because of the presence of insulation, sufficient data were collected to indicate that the vessel had lost an average of 9.3 mils on the inside diameter of that section (see Fig."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 86, "line_start": 86, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "This loss corresponds to 0.045 mils/hr, based on HF exposure time."}
{"claim_type": "figure-reference", "line_end": 86, "line_start": 86, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "However, for comparative purposes, an average rate loss figure of 14.4 mils/month, based on molten salt residence time was also calculated."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 86, "line_start": 86, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "The maximum wall thickness loss in the vapor region of the dissolver, 11 mils, did not deviate greatly from the average quoted."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 88, "line_start": 88, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "In run T-7 the salt level was in the conical section; in all other runs salt contact was from splash."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 88, "line_start": 88, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "The average wall thickness loss found for this section was 4.2 mils, less than the $1\\%$ accuracy of the \"Vidigage\" instrument, although a maximum of 10 mils loss was noted at one point (see Fig."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 88, "line_start": 88, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "Maximum rate losses were 0.049 mils/hr, based on HF exposure time or 15.4 mils/month, based on molten salt residence time."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 90, "line_start": 90, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "The bottom section of the dissolver consists of five cylinders of 5-1/2 inches inside diameter and varying length joined by circumferential welds to form a right cylinder 9 feet in height."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 90, "line_start": 90, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "Excluding the high and low data mentioned, a maximum loss of 6 mils was found for the bottom section."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 100, "line_start": 100, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "${}^{a}$ Based on HF exposure time of 204 hr."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 101, "line_start": 101, "page_hint": null, "section": "LEGAL NOTICE", "text": "Based on molten salt residence time of 465 hr."}
